<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 452/1999 of 1 March 1999 fixing the minimum yields for the granting of aid for the production of fibre flax and hemp </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 452/1999, millega m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks miinimumsaagised kiulina ja kanepi tootmistoetuse andmiseks 1. m&auml;rts 1999 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1308/70 of 29 June 1970 on the common organisation of the market in flax and hemp (1), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 3290/94 (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 29. juuni 1970. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1308/70 lina- ja kanepituru &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 3290/94, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 619/71 of 22 March 1971 laying down general rules for granting aid for flax and hemp (3), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 1420/98 (4), and in particular Article 6 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 22. m&auml;rtsi 1971. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 619/71, milles s&auml;testatakse abi andmise &uuml;ldeeskirjad lina ja kanepi puhul, (3) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1420/98, (4) eriti selle artiklit 6, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1164/89 of 28 April 1989 laying down detailed rules concerning the aid for fibre flax and hemp (5), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 2814/98 (6), lays down the conditions for entitlement to the aid; whereas Regulation (EEC) No 619/71 provides that the Commission can lay down criteria covering normal cultivation work, in particular by setting a minimum yield to be achieved; whereas a minimum yield must be established in order to prevent fibre flax and hemp from being sown not for the sake of production but solely to qualify for a rate of aid higher than that for other arable crops; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: komisjoni 28. aprilli 1989. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 1164/89, milles s&auml;testatakse kiulina ja kanepi puhul antavat toetust k&auml;sitlevad &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad, (5) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 2814/98, (6) s&auml;testatakse toetuse saamise tingimused; m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 619/71 s&auml;testatakse, et komisjon v&otilde;ib kehtestada tavap&auml;raste harimist&ouml;&ouml;de puhul kriteeriumid, eelk&otilde;ige saavutatava miinimumsaagise; miinimumsaagis tuleb kehtestada, et v&auml;ltida kiulina ja kanepi k&uuml;lvamine mitte tootmise eesm&auml;rgil, vaid &uuml;ksnes teiste p&otilde;llukultuuride puhul antavast toetusest k&otilde;rgema m&auml;&auml;raga toetuse saamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Commission Regulation (EC) No 2183/97 (7), lays down the minimum yield to be achieved before aid for fibre flax production can be granted as from the 1998/99 marketing year; whereas experience gained in the course of that marketing year shows that the provisions of that Regulation should be simplified and the minimum yield set should be adjusted accordingly; whereas, for the sake of consistency, a minimum yield to be achieved before aid can be granted for hemp production should also be laid down; whereas Regulation (EC) No 2183/97 should therefore be repealed and new minimum yields to be achieved before aid is granted for fibre flax and hemp production should be laid down on the basis of common principles; </inglise>
<eesti> komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruses (E&Uuml;) nr 2183/97 (7) s&auml;testatakse alates 1998/99. majandusaastast miinimumsaagis, mille saavutamine on kiulina tootmiseks toetuse andmise tingimuseks; k&otilde;nealuse majandusaasta jooksul saadud kogemused n&auml;itavad, et nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse s&auml;tteid tuleks lihtsustada ja miinimumsaagist tuleks vastavalt kohandada; j&auml;rjepidevuse huvides tuleks s&auml;testada miinimumsaagis, mille saavutamine on kanepitootmiseks toetuse andmise tingimuseks; seet&otilde;ttu tuleks kehtetuks tunnistada m&auml;&auml;rus (E&Uuml;) nr 2183/93 ja s&auml;testada &uuml;histe p&otilde;him&otilde;tete alusel uued miinimumsaagised, mille saavutamine on kiulina ja kanepi tootmiseks toetuse andmise eeltingimuseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, to take account of the particular soil and climatic conditions, minimum yields for fibre flax and hemp adapted to the conditions in the main production areas of the Community and corresponding to good cultivation methods should be introduced gradually; whereas, for the sake of simplification, there should be a limit on the number of different minimum yields laid down; </inglise>
<eesti> konkreetsete mullastiku-ja ilmastikutingimuste arvessev&otilde;tmiseks tuleks &uuml;henduse peamiste tootmispiirkondade tingimustega kohandatud kiulina ja kanepi miinimumsaagised ja vastavad head viljelusmeetodid v&otilde;tta kasutusele j&auml;rk-j&auml;rgult; lihtsuse huvides tuleks s&auml;testada erinevate miinimumsaagiste arv; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, to take account of existing cultivation methods, in the United Kingdom in particular, a transitional period should be laid down for that Member State with a view to the gradual introduction of minimum yields corresponding to good cultivation methods; </inglise>
<eesti> eelk&otilde;ige &Uuml;hendkuningriigis kasutatavate viljelusmeetodite arvessev&otilde;tmiseks tuleks k&otilde;nealuse liikmesriigi suhtes kehtestada &uuml;leminekuperiood headele viljelusmeetoditele vastavate miinimumsaagiste j&auml;rkj&auml;rguliseks kasutuselev&otilde;tmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the areas and production on which basis the yield is to be determined should be defined; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleks m&auml;&auml;ratleda piirkonnad ja toodang, mille alusel saagis kindlaks m&auml;&auml;ratakse; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, for cases where the yield found is lower than the minimum yield, Regulation (EC) No 2183/97 provides, on the one hand, for a case-by-case consideration of any exceptional weather conditions and, on the other hand, for the possibility of a gradual reduction in the aid, subject none the less to a threshold percentage of the yield below which no aid is payable; whereas it may not be possible to achieve the minimum yield for several concomitant reasons the individual effects of which are difficult to identify; whereas, despite certain reductions in the minimum yield as a result of this Regulation, the areas in question should not be totally disqualified from the aid but should qualify for reduced aid; whereas provision should be made for a single level of reduced aid which is easy to apply and which does not constitute an incentive against the aid payable on other arable crops; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruses (E&Uuml;) nr 2183/97 on miinimumsaagisest madalama saagise puhul s&auml;testatud &uuml;helt poolt k&otilde;ikide erandlike ilmastikuolude arvessev&otilde;tmine igal konkreetsel juhul ning teiselt poolt v&otilde;imalus toetust j&auml;rk-j&auml;rgult v&auml;hendada kuni k&uuml;nnisprotsendim&auml;&auml;rani, millest v&auml;iksema saagise puhul abi ei maksta; erinevate samaaegselt esinevate p&otilde;hjuste t&otilde;ttu, mille m&otilde;jusid on raske eristada, v&otilde;ib miinimumsaagise saavutamine olla v&otilde;imatu; olenemata teatavatest miinimumsaagise v&auml;hendamistest k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse tulemusel ei tohiks k&otilde;nealuseid piirkondi t&auml;ielikult toetusest ilma j&auml;tta, vaid nende suhtes tuleks kohaldada v&auml;hendatud toetust; tuleks s&auml;testada &uuml;htne v&auml;hendatud toetuse m&auml;&auml;r, mille kohaldamine on lihtne ning mis ei m&otilde;juta teiste p&otilde;llukultuuride suhtes makstavat toetust; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Management Committee for Flax and Hemp has not delivered an opinion within the time limit set by its chairman, </inglise>
<eesti> lina- ja kanepituru korralduskomitee ei ole eesistuja poolt kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaja jooksul oma arvamust avaldanud, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Aid for the production of fibre flax and aid for the production of hemp shall be granted only in respect of areas where the yield of non-deseeded flax straw or non-deseeded hemp straw is at least equal to the following minimums: </inglise>
<eesti> Kiulina ja kanepi tootmistoetust antakse ainult nende alade puhul, kus kupardamata linavarte v&otilde;i raatsimata kanepivarte saagis ei ole madalam kui j&auml;rgmised miinimumsaagised: </eesti>
<inglise> - for areas in Belgium, Denmark, Germany, France, Ireland, Luxembourg, the Netherlands, Austria, Finland, Sweden and the United Kingdom: 2,5 per hectare, </inglise>
<eesti> - Belgias, Taanis, Saksamaal, Prantsusmaal, Iirimaal, Luksemburgis, Hollandis, Austrias, Soomes, Rootsis ja &Uuml;hendkuningriigis asuvates piirkondades: 2,5 tonni hektari kohta, </eesti>
<inglise> - for areas in the other Member States: 1,5 t per hectare. </inglise>
<eesti> - teistes liikmesriikides asuvatel aladel: 1,5 tonni hektari kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> However, the minimum yield of non-deseeded flax straw shall be adjusted as follows for areas in the United Kingdom: </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendkuningriigis asuvate alade puhul kohandatakse kupardamata linavarte miinimumsaagist j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) for the 1999/2000 marketing year: 1,5 t per hectare; </inglise>
<eesti> a) 1999/2000. majandusaastal: 1,5 tonni hektari kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) for the 2000/01 marketing year: 2 t per hectare. </inglise>
<eesti> b) 2000/01. majandusaastal: 2 tonni hektari kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The yield to be used shall be the average yield of non-deseeded straw on the areas covered by aid applications or, where the applicants are growers within the meaning of Article 3a(b) of Regulation (EEC) No 619/71, the yield on the areas of each owner or farmer with whom a contract for flax growing has been concluded. </inglise>
<eesti> Kohaldatav saagis on toetusetaotlusega h&otilde;lmatud alade suhtes kehtestatud kupardamata linavarte keskmine saagis v&otilde;i taotlejad on linakasvatajad m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 619/71 artikli 3a punkti b t&auml;henduses, saagis nende omanike v&otilde;i p&otilde;llumajandustootjate aladel, kellega on s&otilde;lmitud leping lina kasvatamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The average yield as referred to in paragraph 1 shall be equal to the tonnage of non-deseeded straw ready for processing weighed on entry at the processing plant, divided by the area in hectares. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud keskmine saagis on v&otilde;rdne t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisettev&otilde;ttesse toomisel kaalutud, t&ouml;&ouml;tlemiseks valmis kupardamata linavarte tonnaa&zcaron;iga, mis on jagatud alaga hektarites. </eesti>
<inglise> However, </inglise>
<eesti> Siiski: </eesti>
<inglise> - where the straw is harvested separately from the seed, the weight of the seed shall be added to the weight of the straw entering the processing plant, and </inglise>
<eesti> - kui varred koristatakse seemnetest eraldi, lisatakse seemnete mass t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisettev&otilde;ttesse toimetatud varte massile, ja </eesti>
<inglise> - where the straw is harvested using a machine that separates the fibre from the woody parts, the weight of the straw shall be replaced by the total weight of the various products resulting from that separation. </inglise>
<eesti> - kui varred koristatakse masinaga, mis eraldab kiud lina- ja kanepiluudest, asendatakse varte mass eraldamise tulemusena saadud eri toodete kogumassiga. </eesti>
<inglise> Where it is not possible to weigh the woody parts of the stalk, the Member State shall, in the light of the results corresponding to good cultivation methods, establish the weight concerned by means of a coefficient fixed on the basis of on-the-spot checks and the technical specifications of the machine in question. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui lina- ja kanepiluid ei saa kaaluda, m&auml;&auml;rab asjaomase massi headele viljelemistavadele vastavate tulemuste alusel liikmesriik, kasutades selleks koefitsienti, mis m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks kohapealsete kontrollide ja k&otilde;nealuse masina tehniliste n&auml;itajate alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Compliance with the minimum yield shall be established on the basis of the information referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2 available before a date set by the Member State which is before 30 June in the marketing year in question. </inglise>
<eesti> Miinimumsaagise j&auml;rgimine tehakse kindlaks l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 osutatud andmete p&otilde;hjal, mis on k&auml;ttesaadavad liikmesriigi m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htp&auml;eval enne k&otilde;nealuse majandusaasta 30. juunit. </eesti>
<inglise> Where that information reveals that the minimum yield has not been complied with, the Member State shall inform the interested party and, at the latter's request, shall take account, after verification on the spot, of the estimated weight of the quantities relative to the marketing year in question which he is holding in store. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui andmetest selgub, et miinimumsaagist ei ole j&auml;rgitud, teavitab liikmesriik huvitatud isikut ja v&otilde;tab viimase taotluse korral p&auml;rast kohapealset kontrolli arvesse k&otilde;nealusel majandusaastal ladudes olevate koguste hinnangulise massi. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Where the minimum yields laid down in Article 1 are not achieved, the aid payable for the areas in question shall be reduced by 65 %. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui artiklis 1 s&auml;testatud miinimumsaagiseid ei j&auml;rgita, v&auml;hendatakse k&otilde;nealuste alade puhul makstavat toetust 65% v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> Regulation (EC) No 2183/97 shall be repealed with effect from 1 August 1999. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;rus (E&Uuml;) nr 2183/97 tunnistatakse kehtetuks alates 1. augustist 1999. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the seventh day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub seitsmendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall apply from the 1999/2000 marketing year. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat m&auml;&auml;rust kohaldatakse alates 1999/2000. majandusaastast. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 1 March 1999. </inglise>
